name: RNA
description: RNA is conflux/concave music. One man and his Roland Juno 6; improvisatory, serene, pursuing an individual path through the analogue forest. Is this the 70s or the 00s, or now?

name: A.R.P. - 'Music for Broken Rainbows - Live in Paris'
description:
A.R.P use analogue synthesizers and tape effects to create live improvised music that relies on human interaction, chance and relationship feedback, building long loops of sound that change over time. No computers are used, instead A.R.P depend on vintage Roland synthesizers to play live direct on to tape, later editing these long improvisations into discrete tracks.

Michael Atavar – synthesizer, effects
Neil Robinson – synthesizer, effects

name: De Longue Haleine  - 'In Y'
description:
De Longue Haleine create music inspired by the organic context of mountains and skies. Acoustic/electric instruments mix in an environment of minimalist, synthetic sounds.

Pascale Darchy - flute, 
Neil Robinson - double bass, guitar,  synthesizer
